Seven more people have died of COVID-19 in South Africa, the Department of Health announced on Saturday. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Seven more people have died of COVID-19 in South Africa, the Department of Health announced on Saturday. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 6,336. READ: SA lockdown: Cele urges SA to adhere to Level 4 regulations  The Department stated the total number of tests conducted to date is 230,686, of which 13,164 were done in the last 24 hours. Some 235,519 people have died worldwide since the epidemic surfaced in China in December, according to an AFP tally based on official sources. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. - Additional reporting AFP